      "message": "[Major] Line 75: This now gates connectivityChanged() on isCallNotification, but isCallNotification uses remoteMessage.priority rather than originalPriority. That changes the previous high-priority check from original FCM priority to delivered priority, so incoming call pushes that were sent as high priority but delivered/downgraded as normal will no longer trigger network reconnection. The nearby comment also says \u0027HIGH original priority\u0027, which makes the intended behavior ambiguous. Keep the call-type filtering but preserve the original-priority condition.\n```suggestion\n        val isCallNotification \u003d (pushType.contains(\"audioCall\")\n                || pushType.contains(\"videoCall\"))\n                \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.originalPriority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```\nIf the foreground-service start intentionally depends on delivered priority, use two separate booleans so connectivityChanged() continues to use originalPriority.",
